        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 12:44PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1241 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of San Pablo, or 37 miles southeast of San Luis
Valley Airport, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Locally heavy rain of a half inch of rain in 15 minutes
along with gusty winds.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Localized heavy rain could cause local areas of high water
in the region.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central
Costilla and western Las Animas Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>Be alert for rising waters in the region.</instruction>
